parameters: \N<Segi>What is that...?
\N<Irime>Segi...

\N<Segi>Irime-san, what in the world is going on with all this
commotion?

\N<Irime>It seems that as the training competition is drawing to a
close, Luda's people have started to make their move.
They're beginning to plan for what comes after the
competition...

\N<Irime>Those who were defeated in the tournament... or didn't
perform well are starting to be arrested and purged...
They're beginning to transfer them to the main force.

\N<Irime>As a first step for that... it seems they're going to start
executing the prisoners who have already been captured.
\N<Segi>Exe, execution?! You don't mean Lord Yuia is...!?

\N<Irime>No, it doesn't seem to be Yuia-san. The ones they were
talking about are different prisoners. Apparently, two
people have been targeted.
\N<Irime>One of them is the death row inmate Zozoie... that guy.
\N<Segi>Zozoie...

\N<Irime>Even though he participated in the training competition, he
was originally a major criminal. There's nothing
particularly surprising about his case.
\N<Segi>And... who is the other one you mentioned...?

\N<Irime>It's him... the ringleader of that incident. The guy who's
been chained up in the underground of this city for years,
what's-his-name...
\N<Segi>...?

\N<Segi>The execution target wasn't Lord Yuia. But... there's always
a chance of 'what if'. Just to be safe, I should talk to
Zuuteruka...

\N<Irime>...So you're really going? I'm going to miss you.

\N<Segi>Yes... There's been too much happening here. And I think we
played a part in igniting some of those things.

\N<Irime>...I won't ask what it is. But remember, it's not all about
looking back.
\N<Irime>You've helped me out a lot, too. That means more to me.
\N<Segi>If you say so...
\N<Irime>It's not just empty comfort, it's the truth.
\N<Irime>Get along with Yuia-san... and Riia, okay?

\N<Segi>Yes... I'm afraid I might end up making Riia and Rame-chan
feel sad, though.

\N<Irime>That's fine. At their age, those kinds of feelings can be
the very thing that triggers them to confront their true
emotions.
\N<Segi>I hope that's the case...
\N<Segi>...It's about time I left.

\N<Irime>...Yeah. As you said, a lot has happened, but we have to
look forward. If we can't do that, at least we should turn
away from the sad, dark memories and take a good look at
ourselves.

\N<Irime>No matter what happens, the one who stands firm in the end
wins. That's something only those of us who fought in that
damn training corps would understand...
\N<Segi>Irime-san... Thank you.

\N<Segi>...I see no need to answer that question to you. Please

\N<Rozaro>Hmph... I'm disliked, I see. Well, it can't be helped. But

Fine, I'll take my leave for tonight.

\N<Rozaro>Oh yes, before I go, I should give you this. I can't bear to
watch you like this forever.

\N<Rozaro>You know what it is? Mind. A pill that alleviates the

\N<Segi>You... you've had this from the beginning. And you just
overlooked my symptoms...?

it quite interesting to watch.

\N<Rozaro>Hmph... Well then, I shall truly take my leave this time.

himself.
